data.name: python-colorspace
data.description: Python colorspace implementation. Documentation available on https://retostauffer.github.io/python-colorspace/. The latest release is available via the Python Package Index (PyPI) via https://pypi.org/project/colorspace/

evidence: "The package provides a Python 3 version of the R colorspace package" (described as a package/toolbox, indicating it is imported as a library).

Bulleted features such as "Color spaces: Conversions and manipulations" and "matplotlib color maps: Integration with matplotlib for use in standard plotting functions" show it is a reusable component rather than a standalone end-user application.
"PyPI: https://pypi.org/project/colorspace/" indicates distribution via the PyPI package registry.
